verses.roman:
mauhūrtikā deva-gaṇā
muhūrtāyāś ca jajñire
ye vai phalaṁ prayacchanti
bhūtānāṁ sva-sva-kālajam

synonyms: mauhūrtikāḥ—Mauhūrtikas; deva-gaṇāḥ—the demigods; muhūrtāyāḥ—from the womb of Muhūrtā; ca—and; jajñire—took birth; ye—all of whom; vai—indeed; phalam—result; prayacchanti—deliver; bhūtānām—of the living entities; sva-sva—their own; kāla-jam—born of time.
translation: The demigods named the Mauhūrtikas took birth from the womb of Muhūrtā. These demigods deliver the results of actions to the living entities of their respective times.
